The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 June is 43,339 (5,016.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 June, there were 428 new confirmed cases (49.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 June, there were 277 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 55% (151 extra cases).
